New Records: Kumar Rocker tied Don Stanhouse for the second-most strikeouts in Texas Rangers history over their first two MLB appearances
Key Match Events: Rocker struggled with command, allowing two runs on two hits and four walks, while striking out five in three innings.
In the first inning, he allowed a single and a walk before striking out Davis Schneider.
In the second inning, he put the first two batters on with a five-pitch walk and a hit-by-pitch.
In the third inning, he walked the leadoff batter and allowed a sacrifice fly and a check swing strikeout.
Rocker allowed two runs (one earned) on two hits, four walks, and five strikeouts in three innings.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Rocker had Tommy John surgery in May 2023 after being the No. 3 overall pick in the 2022 MLB Draft.
